SMADE ENTERTAINMENT presents their fourth concert of 2018 and the second concert in the month of April – Yemi Alade’s The Black Magic Tour. This will be her first performance at the O2 Academy in London since 2016. The follows the just concluded Falz the Bahd Guy concert. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-609719 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Yemi-Alade-514x598.jpeg" alt="" width="1000" height="1164" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Yemi-Alade-514x598.jpeg 514w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Yemi-Alade-478x557.jpeg 478w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Yemi-Alade-206x240.jpeg 206w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Yemi-Alade-412x480.jpeg 412w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Yemi-Alade-515x600.jpeg 515w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Yemi-Alade.jpeg 640w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /> The London leg of this tour is set to hold on Friday 20th, April 2018 at the O2 Academy, Islington, London.